@Luap99 I think you are right about nginx as journalctl prints a continuous `nginx: [alert] could not open error log file: open() "/var/lib/nginx/logs/error.log" failed (6: No such device or address)`

`sudo ausearch -m avc -ts recent` returned `<no matches>` 

How do I change the log-driver in the quadlet file?

There was a reason why we set the default log-driver to `passthrough`. The original code had this comment:
```
// When running under Systemd use passthrough as the default log-driver.
// When doing so, the journal socket is passed to the containers as-is which has two advantages:
// 1. journald can see who the actual sender of the log event is,
//    rather than thinking everything comes from the conmon process
// 2. conmon will not have to copy all the log data
```
So, the reason for using `passthrough` was not because of Quadlet, but rather because of running under `systemd`. The reason we reverted this change and made it specific for Quadlet was backward compatibility.

Also note that for 4.5, we already have a dedicated key for the LogDriver (for both `.container` and `.kube`) along with the documentation stating that the default is in fact `passthrough` (which I think could have helped in this case).

Furthermore, I think there are different considerations when running under `systemd`. So, while we can have Quadlet use the default from `containers.conf`, I don't see anyone changing it to `passthrough` as it will require anyone running a container from the command line to manually set the log-driver flag.

Having said that, Quadlet started as an opinionated solution and I think we've removed most of its opinions, so what's another one.

We can have it not set anything unless the key is explicitly set
